author: U TEJONMAYAM
description: In a setback for the Indian Space Research Organisation (Isro), the PSLV-C61 mission failed after liftoff from Sriharikota on Sunday. The rocket malfunctioned during its third stage, preventing the EOS-09 satellite from reaching its intended orbit. Isro Chairman V Narayanan cited a drop in chamber pressure within the solid motor as the cause.

author: TNN
description: The US embassy warns of strict action against visa overstays. Foreigners risk deportation and a permanent US entry ban. International visitors staying over 30 days must register. This advisory comes amid rising Indian travel to America. The US is intensifying efforts against visa fraud and illegal immigration. New visa curbs apply to those facilitating illegal immigration.

author: AJAY TOMAR
description: A devastating fire engulfed a century-old building near Charminar in Hyderabad, claiming the lives of 17 members of a jeweller's family. The victims, spanning three generations, had gathered for a weekend. The blaze, suspected to be caused by an electrical short circuit, rapidly spread through the residential-cum-commercial building, trapping the family due to a single narrow exit.

author: TNN
description: In Uttar Pradesh, a cattle smuggler was killed and two others injured in Jaunpur after a police constable was crushed to death during a vehicle chase. author: SWATI DESHPANDE
description: CJI Bhushan Gavai emphasized the Constitution's supremacy, stating that all three branches—judiciary, executive, and legislature—must collaborate within its framework. Justice Gavai highlighted the 'basic structure' doctrine, limiting Parliament's amendment powers.

author: TNN

He emphasized that seeking party recommendations for such delegations has never been a standard practice.

author: ABHIJEET PATIL
description: A devastating fire at a textile factory in Maharashtra's Solapur district claimed eight lives, including a toddler and the factory's owner. The blaze, suspected to be caused by an electrical short circuit, trapped families living on-site. Rescue efforts were hampered by a structure near the entrance, and firefighters faced intense flames and smoke while recovering bodies throughout the day.

author: SUNNY BASKI
title: Hyderabad fire: Miraculous escape for 50 in another fire some 8km away

He aims to combat corruption and modernize the country, focusing on economic development and foreign policy.

author: TNN

author: TNN

author: AJAY TOMAR

Army and IAF units use various air defence systems.

The websites must display key parameters like completion time for 200 flying hours, aircraft availability, instructor details, and simulator access.

The wife's plea for increased maintenance was also dismissed.

description: Amit Shah led a 'Tiranga Yatra' in Ahmedabad to celebrate Operation Sindoor's success, honouring the armed forces for eradicating terrorism. The BJP organized the yatra from May 13-23, commemorating the operation launched in response to the Pahalgam terror attack.
title: Watch: Amit Shah leads 'Tiranga Yatra' in Ahmedabad

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The IPL 2025 made a poignant return after a week-long suspension due to India-Pakistan tensions, commencing with heartfelt tributes to the armed forces. Rajasthan Royals and Punjab Kings united for the national anthem in Jaipur, honouring the soldiers' bravery. Following a washout in Bengaluru, the league's resumption symbolized resilience and gratitude for the nation's defenders.
title: Watch: Emotional tribute to Armed Forces marks IPL 2025 resumption

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mark Scheifele of the Winnipeg Jets played Game 6 against the Dallas Stars shortly after his father's death. He scored the Jets' lone goal in the heartbreaking 2-1 overtime loss, ending their Stanley Cup hopes. Despite personal tragedy, Scheifele's courageous performance and the team's support highlighted the emotional night, with condolences extended by both teams.
title: Winnipeg Jets center Mark Scheifele scores in playoff loss after father's death

title: YouTuber 'spy' was in touch with other influencers, reveal cops

title: 'Cheap political games': Cong slams govt for dropping Op Sindoor delegation nominees

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Vladimir Putin stated Russia's aim to eliminate the causes of the Ukraine war and ensure Russia's security, coinciding with a record drone attack on Ukraine. Despite recent diplomatic talks in Istanbul, which yielded a prisoner exchange agreement, no ceasefire was reached.
title: 'Russia's goal is to eliminate causes of Ukraine war': Putin

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin urged non-BJP ruled states to unite against the Centre's alleged attempt to undermine the Supreme Court's verdict regarding the governor's role. President Murmu sought SC's opinion on its ruling that set deadlines for governors acting on bills. Stalin accused the BJP of using the President to challenge the judgment, potentially impacting states facing uncooperative governors.
title: SC guv verdict: 'Must unite for legal battle', Stalin tells non-BJP state CMs

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Jyoti Malhotra, a YouTuber, has been arrested by Haryana Police on suspicion of espionage. Her father claims she visited Pakistan solely for YouTube content creation with proper permissions. Police allege Malhotra was in contact with Pakistani intelligence, met an officer in Delhi, and shared sensitive information. Authorities seized phones and laptops, registering a case under the Official Secrets Act.
title: Father defends alleged 'spy' YouTuber: 'Can't she call Pak friends?'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) has announced full refunds for ticket holders of the rain-abandoned match against Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) on May 17. Digital ticket holders will receive refunds within 10 working days, while physical ticket holders must return their original tickets at the point of purchase.
title: IPL 2025: RCB announces ticket refunds for abandoned KKR match

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar is embarking on a six-day visit to the Netherlands, Denmark, and Germany starting May 19. Discussions will encompass bilateral relations and global matters. His Germany visit aligns with Friedrich Merz's new role as Federal Chancellor, signaling continued commitment to the India-Germany Strategic Partnership.
title: Jaishankar to visit Netherlands, Denmark, and Germany for bilateral talks

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Russia launched a massive drone attack on Ukraine, deploying 273 drones and decoys, surpassing previous records. Ukrainian air defenses intercepted 88 drones, while electronic interference neutralized 128. The strikes resulted in one death and three injuries in the Kyiv region.
title: Russia launches one of biggest drone attacks on Ukraine since war started

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Army confirms no DGMO-level talks today, says 'no expiry date' of ceasefire

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Ali Khan Mahmudabad, an associate professor at Ashoka University, was arrested following a social media post concerning Operation Sindoor. The arrest, prompted by a complaint from a BJP Yuva Morcha leader, relates to Mahmudabad's remarks about the operation. The Haryana state commission for women had previously issued a notice regarding his comments, which he claims were misunderstood and not anti-women.
title: Ashoka University professor arrested for remarks on Operation Sindoor

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sourav Ganguly expressed surprise at Virat Kohli's recent retirement from Test cricket, following Rohit Sharma's exit. Kohli, India's fourth-highest Test run-scorer, leaves a significant void. Ganguly acknowledged it's a personal decision but emphasized the selectors' crucial role in choosing the next Test captain, considering long-term implications and Bumrah's injury situation, ahead of the England series.
title: Former India captain questions Virat Kohli's retirement from Test cricket

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The IMF has imposed 11 new conditions on Pakistan's bailout program, raising the total to 50, and cautioned that escalating tensions with India could jeopardize fiscal and reform objectives. These conditions include parliamentary approval of the federal budget, agricultural income tax reforms, and liberalization of used car imports.
title: IMF issues strong warning, sets 11 new conditions for Pak amid tensions with India

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sourav Ganguly voiced optimism about Eden Gardens hosting the 2025 IPL final, emphasizing the strong relationship between CAB and BCCI. Despite protests, he believes the issue will be resolved.
title: 'It's Eden's playoffs': Sourav Ganguly confident of hosting IPL 2025 final

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Zoho's Sridhar Vembu cautioned software engineers about the potential for job losses due to advancements in AI and large language models. He emphasized that high compensation in the software industry isn't guaranteed and urged professionals to remain adaptable.
title: Zoho co-founder to software engineers: High salaries are not ‘birthright’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A powerful bomb exploded outside a fertility clinic in Palm Springs, California, resulting in one fatality and multiple injuries. The FBI has declared the incident an act of terrorism, launching a large-scale investigation. Authorities are working to determine the motive and whether the attack was domestic or international, while also investigating if the explosion was livestreamed.
title: Bomb blast outside California fertility clinic: What we know so far

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US authorities have rejected fifteen mango shipments from India at various airports due to documentation irregularities concerning mandatory irradiation treatment. Exporters face approximately $500,000 in losses as they were compelled to dispose of the fruit locally due to high re-exportation costs.
title: Forced to destroy! US rejects mango shipments from India

author: SHANKAR RAGHURAMAN
description: With 12 league games remaining, CSK, RR, SRH, and KKR are out of playoff contention. GT, RCB, and PBKS are almost certain to advance, while MI and DC have a fair chance, and LSG's chances are slim. Despite 4,096 possible result combinations, probabilities suggest RCB, GT, and PBKS have high chances of making the top four. For instance, GT finish in the top two in 2,800 of the possible combinations of match outcomes, translating to a 68.4% chance of being first or second, singly or jointly.
title: IPL playoffs scenarios: Gujarat Titans have 99.2 % chance of progressing

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli's unexpected retirement from Test cricket has elicited varied reactions, with former coach Ravi Shastri suggesting mental fatigue. Sanjay Bangar, ex-batting coach, expressed sadness but respected Kohli's conviction, acknowledging his significant impact on Indian cricket. Kohli's 14-year Test career saw him amass 9,230 runs, transforming India into a formidable force.
title: 'Letting go is not appreciated in our country': Sanjay Bangar on Virat Kohli

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Microsoft recently laid off approximately 6,000 employees, impacting various levels and teams. Gabriela de Queiroz, Director of AI for Startups, was among those affected, expressing sadness but maintaining a positive outlook. The layoffs coincide with Microsoft's aggressive push into AI, even as software engineers and AI leadership roles were impacted by the cuts.
title: Microsoft's fired AI director to 6,000 laid off employees: 'These are people who…'

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: NASA's James Webb Space Telescope has achieved a groundbreaking feat by definitively detecting crystalline ice water in the young star system HD 181327, located 155 light-years away. This marks the first time frozen water has been found outside our solar system, offering crucial insights into the composition of distant planetary systems.
title: NASA's discovers frozen water around a star, insights into planet formation

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The PDP has strongly criticized Omar Abdullah's remarks regarding the Tulbul Navigation Project and the Indus Waters Treaty, cautioning that such statements could destabilize the fragile peace along the Line of Control. The party deemed Abdullah's comments as irresponsible, especially given the current volatile climate.
title: PDP slams Omar over call to scrap Indus Waters Treaty

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'Planned, trained & executed': Army shares new video of Operation Sindoor

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The Trump administration's abrupt suspension of IMLS grants has triggered widespread disruption in US libraries. States are facing staff layoffs, suspension of interlibrary loans, and reduced access to digital resources. This financial shortfall impacts rural communities disproportionately, hindering access to e-books and vital library services, prompting legal challenges and raising concerns about the future of library funding.
title: Why can’t you borrow that e-book anymore? Trump’s order hits US libraries hard

author: SUNNY BASKI AND AJAY TOMAR
description: A significant fire erupted early Sunday in Guzar House, near Hyderabad's Charminar, prompting a swift emergency response. Fire department officials, alerted around 6:30 am, found numerous unconscious individuals within the building. Approximately 20 people were rushed to nearby hospitals for treatment, according to an AIMIM legislator who visited the site.
title: 17 killed, several injured after fire breaks out in building near Hyderabad's Charminar

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: ISRO's PSLV-C61 mission faced a setback as the launch of Earth Observation Satellite EOS-09 failed due to a technical anomaly in the third stage. The mission, intended to place EOS-09 in a Sun Synchronous Polar Orbit for high-resolution imaging, encountered the issue after normal performance in the initial stages. Analysis is underway to determine the cause.
title: 'Mission could not be accomplished': What Isro chief said after EOS-09 setback

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: As IPL 2025 nears its playoff stage, Royal Challengers Bengaluru leads with 17 points, needing just one more win to secure their spot. Gujarat Titans are also well-positioned, while Punjab Kings require one victory from their remaining matches. Mumbai Indians face a must-win situation in their two remaining games. With multiple teams still in the hunt, the final week promises high-stakes drama and potential surprises.
title: Race to the playoffs! Shocking twists in IPL qualification scenarios

author: MANVIR SAINI
description: Haryana police arrested Jyoti Malhotra, a travel vlogger from Hisar, for allegedly spying and sharing sensitive information with Pakistan. She is accused of promoting positive narratives about Pakistan on social media and maintaining contact with a Pakistani official, Ehsan-ur-Rahim, who was later expelled from India. The investigation revealed multiple trips to Pakistan and connections with intelligence operatives.
title: 'Visited Pak over 4 times': YouTuber linked to Pakistani intel officer

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tragedy struck as the Mexican Navy training ship Cuauhtémoc collided with the Brooklyn Bridge, resulting in two fatalities and injuring at least seventeen others. The ship, carrying 277 people, reportedly lost power, causing its masts to strike the bridge. Eyewitnesses described a chaotic scene with sailors dangling from the damaged masts.
title: Watch: Chaos as Mexican ship collides with Brooklyn Bridge, sailors seen dangling

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: The NASA Extravehicular Mobility Unit (EMU) spacesuit is a vital piece of equipment for astronauts performing spacewalks. It protects them from the harsh environment of space, providing thermal insulation, radiation shielding, and impact resistance. The EMU also includes a life support system with oxygen, carbon dioxide removal, water, and temperature control, ensuring astronauts' survival during long EVAs.
title: What makes Nasa’s spacesuit crucial for surviving & how it protects astronauts

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aishwarya Rai and Abhishek Bachchan, along with their daughter Aaradhya, created a heartwarming family moment by dancing to 'Kajra Re' at a Mumbai event. The video, shared by Rahul Vaidya, shows Aishwarya gracefully dancing while Abhishek and Aaradhya cheer her on, all dressed in matching white-cream outfits. This delightful display of family unity has captured hearts across social media.
title: Aishwarya, Abhishek, and Aaradhya dance together as Rahul Vaidya sings ‘Kajra Re’

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: The U.S. Embassy in India has issued a warning about the consequences of overstaying visas. Indian citizens traveling to the U.S. on work, student, or tourist visas risk deportation and a permanent ban if they remain beyond their authorized stay.
title: US Embassy in India issues warning of permanent ban on traveling: If you...

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold prices are under pressure, having fallen 7% from their April high, testing a crucial support level. Analysts suggest further declines are possible if key support levels break, influenced by reduced expectations for US rate cuts and diminished trade war concerns.
title: Will gold prices drop to Rs 88,000 per 10 grams? Experts see downside

author: KALYAN DAS
description: A junior resident doctor at AIIMS-Rishikesh faces charges of promoting enmity after allegedly distributing sweets following a terror attack in Pahalgam. A VHP district president filed the complaint, claiming the act hurt sentiments and appeared to celebrate the killings.
title: Doctor booked for distributing 'Eid sweets' day after Pahalgam attack

author: TNN
description: Shashi Tharoor's acceptance of a government nomination for a global outreach team has stirred controversy within the Congress party, especially after his comments on the conflict with Pakistan. Jairam Ramesh criticized the government's nomination process as dishonest. BJP leaders questioned Congress's decision not to nominate Tharoor, citing potential jealousy or intolerance.
title: Govt's diplomatic outreach team: Congress has tough call to take as rift with Tharoor widens

author: KUMAR MUKESH
description: Hisar, a key military center in Haryana, faces renewed national security concerns following the arrest of a local YouTuber for alleged espionage. With a history of ISI activity spanning over two decades, the city, home to vital military assets, has been a target for Pakistani intelligence.
title: Spy whispers refuse to subside in Hisar after arrest of vlogger Jyoti Malhotra

author: TNN
description: In Shravasti, Mohammed Saifuddin was arrested for the murder of his wife, Sakina, after she allegedly nagged him about being unemployed. Saifuddin confessed to killing Sakina, chopping her body into pieces, and disposing of them in a forest and a pond.
title: 'Used to beat her for dowry': UP man chops wife’s body into pieces

author: VIJAY SINGH
description: Sanjay Raut's new book, ‘Narkatla Swarg', alleges Bal Thackeray helped Amit Shah secure bail in an encounter case and Sharad Pawar opposed Narendra Modi's arrest after the Godhra riots. The book launch, attended by prominent opposition leaders, sparked controversy, with BJP leaders demanding investigation into Raut's claims about judicial process.
title: Balasaheb helped Amit Shah get bail, claims Sanjay Raut in his book

author: ASSEEM SHAIKH
description: The NIA arrested two absconders, Abdullah Faiyaz Shaikh and Talha Khan, at Mumbai airport upon their arrival from Jakarta. They are key members of an ISIS sleeper module involved in fabricating IEDs in Pune back in 2023.
title: 'Conspired to commit terror acts': NIA arrests two Isis members at Mumbai airport

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Jyoti Malhotra, a travel vlogger with a significant online presence, has been arrested for allegedly spying for Pakistan. She maintained contact with Pakistani intelligence, attended events at the Pakistan High Commission, and frequently praised Pakistan on social media. Investigations reveal she shared sensitive information and received assistance from Pakistani officials for visa extensions and stays during her visits.
title: In her own YouTube videos, proof of vlogger Jyoti Malhotra links to Pakistan revealed

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: MS Dhoni's immense popularity in Chennai and across India is undeniable, with fans displaying unwavering support for 'Thala.' Harbhajan Singh emphasized the genuine affection Dhoni receives, distinguishing it from manufactured social media followings. Meanwhile, things haven’t gone CSK’s way over the past two seasons. ​​​The five-time IPL champions failed to reach the playoffs in 2024 and endured another underwhelming campaign in IPL 2025.
title: Shocking statement! 'Asli fans Dhoni ke hain, baaki sab paid'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: At the 15 and the Mahomies charity gala in Las Vegas, Travis Kelce shared a heartwarming moment with Patrick Mahomes' sister, Mia. An Instagram post captured Kelce and Mia's genuine smiles, radiating a sense of family. The event, filled with love and purpose, supported Patrick's foundation, emphasizing meaningful connections and positive impact.
title: Travis Kelce bonds with Mahomes’ sister Mia at gala, wins Swift family nod

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A Mexican Navy training vessel, the Cuauhtémoc, collided with the Brooklyn Bridge while sailing on the East River, causing visible damage to the ship's mast. The incident, captured in viral videos, showed the mast striking the bridge, adorned with a large Mexican flag. Authorities are investigating the collision, with no immediate reports of injuries or damage to the bridge structure.
title: Watch: Mexican naval vessel hits New York's Brooklyn Bridge

author: SWEDHA RADHAKRISHNAN
description: Chennai's Rajiv Gandhi Govt General Hospital faces severe criticism for its emergency ward's dire conditions. Patients and families report extensive delays for CT scans due to equipment shortages. They also allege demands for bribes for basic services like wheeling patients and providing essential items.
title: Roaches, rats & graft: What greets patients at this Chennai govt hospital

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Devastating tornadoes and severe storms have ripped through Kentucky, Missouri, and Virginia, resulting in at least 27 fatalities and numerous injuries. Kentucky was hit hardest, with 18 deaths, while Missouri experienced significant damage from an EF-3 tornado in St. Louis.
title: 'Could feel the vibration': At least 27 killed as violent storms rip through US

author: U TEJONMAYAM
description: ISRO's PSLV-C61 mission, intended to deploy the EOS-09 earth observation satellite, failed after normal performance until the second stage. An observation during the third stage led to the mission's incompletion. This was the third failure for PSLV, despite the vehicle performing as expected in the initial phases. EOS-09 aimed to enhance India's earth observation capabilities with its advanced radar imaging.
title: Isro's PSLV-C61/EOS-09 launch mission fails

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Suresh Raina advocates for Virat Kohli to receive the Bharat Ratna, recognizing his significant contributions to Indian cricket. Raina emphasized Kohli's achievements and impact on the nation's cricketing landscape, urging the Indian government to bestow the prestigious award upon him. Kohli recently retired from Test cricket, marking the end of an era.
title: 'Virat Kohli deserves Bharat Ratna'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Chennai Super Kings have faced disappointing seasons, leading to intense fan rivalry, particularly with RCB. Robin Uthappa criticized some RCB fans for mocking CSK's suspension with 'CSK jail' jerseys and heckling supporters, deeming it unsportsmanlike. Meanwhile, RCB's victory and KKR's washout have significantly impacted the IPL playoff race, with RCB now leading the points table.
title: 'CSK in jail for two years ... ': Fans slammed for mocking Dhoni

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Delhi Capitals are contemplating promoting KL Rahul to the opener position for their crucial IPL 2025 match against Gujarat Titans. Rahul is on the verge of becoming the fastest Indian to score 8000 T20 runs, needing just 33 runs to surpass Virat Kohli's record. However, Rashid Khan of Gujarat Titans could pose a threat to Rahul's milestone.
title: KL Rahul set to break Virat Kohli's massive T20 record

author: PATRICIA COHEN
description: The United Arab Emirates is significantly increasing its economic influence in Africa, investing heavily in key sectors like ports, mining, and renewable energy. With the United States and China reducing their presence, the UAE has pledged billions in deals, surpassing other nations' investments. This strategic move aims to diversify the UAE's economy and capitalize on Africa's resources and strategic location.
title: UAE pours money into Africa, seeking resources, power
